Yum.  Tacos were excellent and service was prompt and friendly.
Looks like and is the perfect hole in the wall with fabulous, delicious and flavorful Mexican food.  Great place to eat at this destination area in DC.
Enjoyed the Nachos for sure!

The owner/general manager needs to attend a class in customer service.  Strolled by yesterday (Thursday) around 4:30pm. I noticed several open tables outside and had my husband pick one out while I went inside to ask someone if they were available and if they had happy hour deals. I asked the man with a tablet in his hand the questions and he said yes. I asked if we could sit “there” and pointed to where my husband was standing, and the man mumbled under his breath “Sure, this is McDonalds”.  Needless to say, we just left after that.  All he could’ve said was “We’re taking reservations, but let me see what we can do”.  You don’t have to be rude - and if you don’t want to be compared to McDonald’s, don’t act like some of their associates.
Excellent tacos and margaritas. New favorite on 14th st.
Good place to eat

Pleasantly surprised by the amount of vegan options for those who are plant based! We ate outside on the patio and the service was great. I went inside once to use the restroom once, and there were more guests without masks than I would feel comfortable with, but all staff were being safe as possible (tip them well!). Would definitely go back, but only outside!
Outstanding service and food! One of a kind burritos!!

Unreal vibes inside that give off to be a trendy lounge .  The bar and drinks are great - homemade tequila infused with pineapple drinks are a must.  Great food to share with, and I highly recommend having the street elote (street corn).  The tacos and burritos have many different in-house made sauces that elevate these dishes to another level.
Tacos were decent quality. Excellent margaritas and quick delivery.
Very tasty pulled pork and steak tacos! They have gluten free shells as well. Cocktails are great and the staff are friendly. I wish they had gluten free corn chips but the tacos make up for it.

Great food, below average service and the bartender serving drinks... With no mask on... Think of the outbreak from one person alone. And I pretty sure the manager saw this several times and didn't enforce anything

Good and masked up atmosphere. The servers are nice, knowledgeable and polite. Manager introduced himself and was cool and curtious.  Food is great and the bartender Ms. Chris is an awesome ball of energy who makes a mean cocktail 🍸

The food was great. I ordered street corn, and 4 different tacos... jumbo shrimp, crispy fish, the cod, and picadillo. I was only a fan of the crispy fish and shrimp. I wish they had more options for sides but this isn't traditional Mexican food. Nevertheless I'd go back here again for sure! Also... their packaging for delivering tacos is the best I've seen. Nothing was soggy or a mess. The corn had lost it's cheese but I could deal with that lol.  ***Updating to 5 stars. We ordered again 2 days later knowing what we liked on the menu and everything was perfect. Plus they have the fastest delivery!
It’s not authentic Mexican restaurant that’s for sure. Food was ok but not to my liking. I love their street corn it’s real good.
Not real mexican food.....
The bartender was outstanding! Excellent energy between the staff and my food was amazing. Look forward to arriving earlier in the future.
Great food and staff!
The plant nachos and Smokey margaritas are incredible.  Can’t go wrong with any of their tacos, all are delicious.  Friendliest staff and superb service!

I went here for my second time last weekend. The service hasn't been good either time. The waitress' don't have much knowledge of the menu and have been extremely slow, leaving us turning our heads looking for them. I got the mezcal flight which was accompanied with salt and lime as if it were a tequila shot, which was disappointing.

Love their food with loads of veg options and creative spin on Mexican bbq. Their outdoor seating is perfectly spaced but they do not do reservations for outdoor seating, so if you make a reservation, you may still end up waiting for a seat outside. Their Mexican mule drink is phenomenal!
no al pastor tacos but not too bad, nice wait staff
Very cute place. Yummy food
Incredible food and atmosphere and the servers are so kind! I loved it and miss going!

Delicious drinks, tasty tacos, fun atmosphere, the guacamole disappoints. Very much enjoyed the Smoky Margarita with mezcal (tried the Frida Mezcal a little sweater)  The quesaritos are a must try, delicious the Jambalaya one. The other tacos were good too, pork and Nashville Hot Chicken (warning, it is fried).  Guacamole was bland and the chips were a little stale  Good service, enthusiastic staff, and very reasonable prices  Great social distancing practices: all staff wearing masks, outdoor and well spaced indoor seating, digital menu, contactless payment options, and plenty of hand sanitizer available for customers

My boyfriend and I ordered the lobster tacos and jumbo shrimp tacos for Taco Tuesday last night and they were AMAZING! We ordered our meal for pick up and our food was ready, hot and fresh, right at the time we had scheduled our pick up for. The shrimp in the Jumbo Shrimp Tacos were cooked perfectly and so flavorful. The lobster in the Lobster tacos was so fresh and tender. Also very very flavorful. When picking up the food at the bar, I also ordered Mojitos (not an option for online ordering, which I wish it was) which were made perfectly; the only piece of constructive criticism that I’d have to give is for the price of the Mojitos, I would’ve appreciated a little bit of a larger to-go cup. Nonetheless, we’ll definitely be back to Mexicue and I look forward to spending many more Taco Tuesdays here!
Great food and there just aren’t many places where I can get vegan nachos! Super wonderful service as well.
Great food

never delivered our food... bummer was excited to try it.in addition my girlfriend and I called them a total of 19 times. Their phones do NOT work. Don’t waste your time or money here. I sure hope they’ll be giving us a full refund. I also wish I knew how to contact them. Clearly we aren’t the only ones. Had pretty high hopes but it is not worth it. Plenty of other places that I’m sure have equally good food and far better service .

(Original) La comida es excelente, el único detalle es que la mesonera no hablaba español que es lo que yo espero de un restaurante de comida mexicana.
Great taco combinations. Drinks are delicious

Beware before you order delivery. Tried it for the first time delivery last night. We had someone in our group who is dairy free. No where on the order to comment or write it. None of the phone numbers work. Even called the New York location to try and connect us (they couldn’t). Couldn’t call to tell them no dairy and of course came with a bunch of dairy. Ended up having to order something else. We got the brisket burnt end tacos, pork tacos, smoked chicken tacos, street corn, cornbread and the chips/salsa (also forgot the guacamole). Overall the food was ok but the service and lack of communication given a significant allergy was terrible.
The food and drinks are pretty good! Only thing I would say is that the menu is a little limited. I love their nachos! I added chicken and guac for an extra fee.
I will definitely go back
Had the quesaritos, delicious!

Mexicue is one of my favorite places in DC because of the atmosphere. It has this really good vibe to it, all the servers are friendly and it really feels like a place you could become a local at. The decor is absolutely gorgeous, the food is fantastic and the drinks are out of this world. I have had their margaritas –and let me tell you they have all sorts of crazy ones. But so good!!!! + food is beyond amazing. I have had the street corn, all of their tacos, even with the lettuce boats, the QUESARRITOS WHICH ARE AMAZING AS WELL, and their guac and I can say there's nothing like it in DC. –– During the quarantine I also ordered online and I thought it would be messy, and it was pristine and so well-packed, just great take-out packaging, but definitely missed the atmosphere and can't wait to go again once we get back to "the new normal"
First time there and I loved it. Food was full of flavor. I wish they had more meat options, but that won't deter me from returning.
Fish tacos (both the crispy one and the fried one) were the bomb .com
Had a really lovely meal here. The salad we had was fresh and excellent as well as the tacos
Great place great atmosphere great staff.
Food, atmosphere & service were all great
Food is good, service was kinda slow and the decor/ambiance was nice but all the way inside at the back got stuffy after a while
Very disappointing food just average
Food was amazing and so was the service!
Good mezcal cocktail, chill bartender, nice vibe

I've been here several times with my partner and we really loved the food however the past two times we've gotten it we've had issues. We both always order vegetarian food because one of us is vegetarian and the other eats halal but the last time we sat in our food had two pieces of sausage randomly in it. It's been a while so today we decided to try again and ordered take away and it happened again. It would be appreciated if they could pay closer attention to these things to accommodate people's religious and dietary restrictions.

First time here at Mexicue. We were sat immediately though it seemed crowded and busy. Our waitress was, Alexa, she was speedy with our drink orders and gave us ample time to order.  I ordered a margarita on the rocks and to be frank it was delicious and delivered a fresh flavor. For dinner I had the BBQ Pulled Pork Bowl. Though unlisted, it does come in a small for an individual order, otherwise the regular size would have been enough for 4 people. Thank you Alexa for that. The food was rather tasty and filling. Alexa's shift ended and we were given to another server...  After dinner, I ordered the Tres Leche, however it didn't really resemble what I anticipated. It was literally a block of corn bread, severely dry and overly spiced; the hint of cinnamon was overstated. It was topped with a tiny portion of vanilla ice cream and drizzled with a meager amount of caramel. It was unfinished. Upon the server's return I asked for a box for the remainder of spiced corn bread, the supposed Tres Leche, and asked if I can have more caramel sauce to go.  This is what really peeved me, the server exclaims that the caramel is the most important ingredient of this dessert and cannot be placed into a to go ramiken because the chef will need to prepare it from scratch. Really? He then goes on and explains to me the steps on making the dessert as if I had asked. I used to work as a sous chef and I'm certain the caramel is in fact in a filled squirt bottle, for easy use in topping and garnishing. In other words the server was too lazy to accommodate me. To go on and on with why he couldn't fulfill my request, tells a lot about their work ethic.  This would have been 2 stars if he was our initial server. Food was great but the service was questionable. Don't order the Tres Leche, it's not quite the same as what it should be.

Stepped in on a whim Sunday afternoon, and did NOT regret it! Great atmosphere, welcoming, greeted by several friendly folks, who gave a quick tour of the menu. I had two incredibly flavorful and unique dishes! The roasted cashew queso was warm, smooth and had a subtle heat that just, served with some of the best chips I've ever had in a restaurant. The Mexican jambalaya small bowl hit all the right flavor notes for me, too. My server Ryan was terrific - friendly, great smile and gave me the history of the restaurant. I now understand why the place had the fun food truck/street food vibe. I'll be back on future visits to DC!
Awesome staff, location and food. Great addition to the neighborhood
Drinks and staff are great but food is not too attractive.

The food was not very good, so overly seasoned I could barely taste the food. Small wine menu and the red I had was not very good. Vibe was vibrant. A fast casual place (they brought a machine over for you to pay) priced like a full fledge restaurant.

Cute Mexican restaurants on 14th st! Highly recommend trying their quesarittos! Their portion is small so I suggest ordering two small dishes per person. I shared a large mac and cheese and had a quesaritto for myself. Other than a slow service, overall it was a good experience.

If you are in the area it's a solid choice for margaritas and cocktails. Tequila and mezcal enthusiast will likely find something here that they enjoy.  After being here several times I don't think I would recommend the food. When I ordered tacos, the tortillas were barely warm and the shrimp/veggies were not very flavorful. I felt the same way about the bowls (mostly romaine lettuce).  The service is okay but could be way better. I remember being seated and waiting a long time for a menu or my order to be taken. I've sat at the bar several times to ask for tequila and mezcal recommendations/substitutions and I found the staff was not as knowledgeable/unprepared compared to other tequila/mezcal bars.
Simply put the food here was magnificent!! The atmosphere was very relaxing
Drinks and food...equally as delicious.  Decor was gorgeous...you can tell it has New York roots.  The service was a little slow...but it was because they had new employees working that day.
Cool spot

Really good food but the seating area where you walk in is pretty cramped. We felt like we were on top of the table next to us. Service was also just a tad slow though it was busy for brunch. Good deals on Tecates at brunch!
The food was very good. The beer taps weren't working, and the fryers weren't working. Other than that, great food, attentive staff. I will be back to try more things.

I was really excited to try this newish Mexican restaurant on 14th. Had a reasonable wait on a Saturday night and it smelled great so what could go wrong? We walked up after receiving a text message saying our table was ready and no one spoke to or made eye contact with us for about 5 minutes. We watched them clean a bunch of tables off them finally, just as I was about to say something, a gentleman asked to take us to our seat while the hostess continued to ignore us as we stood right in front of her, strike 1 of the night. I immediately notice its larger than I expected and were taking to a little orange cave to dine. Someone came with water and to take our drink order pretty quickly but let us know there’d be a small wait to receive our drinks because the bar was backed up. 35 minutes later we finally receive our pitcher of house margarita. We ordered two entrees and guacamole. Our food came out faster than our drinks but our guacamole never arrived and our waitress became a ghost. Our food was cold as it was brought to the table so I assume it’s be hanging out in the back somewhere for a while. Starving and losing patience, we continued to eat our cold meal rather than take on the responsibility of hunting down our waitress or a manager, strike 2. We stop some other poor man as he’s cleaning a table to ask about dessert and he lets us know all they have is a brownie sundae. Perfect, it’s quick and simple. The sundae comes out the fastest of anything we ordered that night BUT the bottom of it is BURNT to a crisp. Again, no one stopped by to ask how our food was or if we were satisfied with our experience thus far, strike 3. It took another 15-20 minutes to hunt down our waitress for the check and guess what, we were charged for the guacamole that never came. She didn’t apologize or flinch when she realized she’s never checked on us nor brought out our food. She just casually took it off the check and charged us. We were in the restaurant for almost 3 hours and I can count the times our waitress came to our table on one hand, with fingers to spare. Once we finally left, I thought, at least my nachos were good, cold but delicious. WRONG. My friend and I spent the next several hours with HORRIBLE stomach aches. She was told the chili was vegetarian since she’s a pescatarian, but we’re almost sure there was meat in it and that’s what caused her immediate discomfort. I on the other hand eat meat and nachos regularly and have NEVER had an adverse reaction like this. I won’t be coming back until they do a full overhaul of staff and cooks. Hot food, cold drinks, and decent service come a dime a dozen in DC. If this place wants to survive, they have a lot of work to do. I also have yet to hear back from a representative of the restaurant despite reaching out as requested below.

LOVE this new spot on 14 St. I've been three times now and I will keep going back. The taco prices are very reasonable for the area and I love the margs there. They always have a special flavor marg.  Neat vibe, decor, and music. Love all the plants and colorful lights. Will be back for sure!

Happened to stumble upon Mexicue yesterday when looking for a place to go to on 14th ST. It is a great place to go if you are looking for a casual but fun place with really good drinks, food offering, and atmosphere. I got the Frida Mezcal which was delicious and really like the food I got. They were accommodating to my no dairy request which was great. Also, have to mention how friendly and personable the host and server were. Definitely will be going back!
food is good but a little overpriced.

caption: Nice place! It was very crowded when we came on a Saturday night, a 45-minute wait. Love the Margarita! Guac is reallh delicious as well. The tacos are just fine for me. Our server was quick and friendly. We got her whenever we need even though the place was packed!
Randomly stopped here for nachos and margaritas, it was surprisingly good.
Amazing
The seating is a bit tight, but the food is light and delicious

I had the nachos. It was good but nothing crazy good. Was lacking guac. The chips were more crunchy than I like.  Also got the mac n cheese. There was a while layer of cheese on the top that wasnt melted. It was okay but the pasta was so soft it blended in w the cheese.  Tacos were way too expensive. My friend who got 3 tacos thought 2/3 were too spicy.
Food is a fusion experience, will be back all the way from Chicago!!!!
Food was pretty good but service was so slow and several problems with our order and bill.
Tacos are delicious, possibly my favorite in DC. Although the drinks and appetizers are overpriced. Worth it to opt for a pitcher and the foursome of dips!
The drinks are on point, the tacos amazing, this place is great n the service phenomenal. Love all the wait staff and bartenders. And their gm is too cool and personable!
Bomb food, great drinks, and amazing vibe. Ask for Chieu she's so cute, nice, and fun!!
Great service and good food. Some of the best Mexican cuisine I’ve had in DC. Mixed drinks are reason for 4, not 5, stars. They are weak, over iced and expensive for what you get.
Food was decent, but ambiance and service were poor. Incredibly loud and 45 minutes to turn around tacos...
Good delicious food

My husband and I went to Mexicue for date night and were very impressed with both the food and the service! Our server Ryan was very sweet, helpful, and prompt all night. We are both vegetarian and the menu had great options for us to choose from. The grilled cornbread was delicious, and the vegetarian picadillo taco was fanastic. Plus we topped it all off with the poblano mac n cheese which I would highly recommend!!  My husband had a delicious margarita and they also had a selection of mocktails, which was perfect for my dry January.  And  I would highly recommend Mexicue!

I went with some friends and waited close to 2 hours for food. It was a bad sign when it took 20 minutes to get water to the table and order food. After waiting an hour for food, we pulled aside a waitress who was not our own (bc ours was nowhere to be seen for a while) and notified her that we’d been waiting over an hour for food. The manager came over, never apologized, stated the kitchen was busy and our food would be out in a few minutes. This felt like a lie bc people who came in after us had already gotten there food and left. More likely, our order was never put in. After waiting another 20 minutes, our group left. The waitress who helped us apologized as we left and looked like she was doing her job well. Worst restaurant/bar experience ever
Lots of flavor and good portions. Taxos and bowls on point.
The best Mexican food I’ve ever had!!! You have to give them a try if you’re in DC. Please open a restaurant in New York!!

Fabulous dinner tonight at Mexicue with a friend.  The grilled cornbread with special honey butter was insane! Great staff and service, fast delivery of food, etc.  We enjoyed chatting with Kendra at the end of our meal.  Can’t wait to return!

Missed opportunities. Visited Friday night without reservations, told the wait time was 30-35 minutes (actual was 45 minutes). There is no convenient wait space as they have crammed every table possible in the square footage. Drinks were not good nor well made. After ordering them, we realized bartenders were looking at recipe sheets (under the register) for every drink.  Wait times were unnecessary, if the management focused on overall speed of service. Our server never returned after the food was delivered and our second round of drinks never made it by the end of the meal.  The food was expected and over priced comparable to the DC market.This restaurant has a long way to go to be on par with the numerous other options delivering better service, similar food. If bartenders need recipes for every drink, they should be in training...not serving on a Friday night.
Food is great. We wanted to try everything! Highly recommend the lobster taco. Sit at the bar. Lafawn is a wonderful bartender!

This restaurant was  amazing!! it was a fun and hip place to eat with amazing food. Portions are small but not overpriced. We got the street corn tostada and the tuna ceviche tostada which were both DELICIOUS with a beautiful display. Would highly recommend going to this restaurant!
Food was good atmosphere is cool.

The music was quite loud for such a small space. Drinks took absolutely forever and the service was inattentive. We had to put in our order with a server that wasn't assigned to our table. My margarita was quite good, though.  The food was good, but it tasted like it had been sitting a while. The theme for the evening seemed to be "slow". There was a bit too much "crema" in all of the offerings we selected. It overpowered the flavor of the meat and salsas.  I think I'd go back, but not sure if it's really worth the money—the prices were pretty high.

Food was decent but a little over the going price for the area. Our server was terrible but had help from others to make up for it. Overall:good but def better taco places that are cheaper in the area
Super friendly staff and great drinks and appetizers

Having been here 3 or 4 times spanning across brunch and dinner, the food is pretty good but the prices just make this place unbearable. My main gripe is that the portions are absolutely tiny compared to the prices being charged -- for both food and drink. Nearly all of the specialty cocktails listed on the wall, which are once again on the smaller side relative to price, go for no less than $13, most around $14. In addition, a side of bacon for brunch is $4 for 1 slice of bacon and every other entree is just petite sized.  My most recent brunch visit I had the cornbread french toast, which having had the cornbread with a previous dinner and it being delicious, I was excited for. Perhaps having incorrectly thought "cornbread french toast" would be a "french toast" twist on the cornbread, I was sorely disappointed to find that it was literally the exact same cornbread served with dinner simply with sides of whip cream, honey, and pineapple -- at nearly double the already high side price for cornbread.  Having given this place multiple tries, I will not be back here unless they change the prices or serving sizes -- sad to say seeing as there's been a lot of excitement for both The Meatball Shop previously and now Mexicue. It seems that management has simply not realized that their prices are far too high for the area at this point.
A fresh take on good traditional foods and excellent service

Spent more than $100 there one night, but the next morning I noticed they put extra charges on my card. Called back and spoke with Lynn, Director of Operations for Mexicue, and  instead of refunding the items I didn't order or even sign the receipt for, she told me to have my bank take care of it. Horrible customer service, and by middle management nonetheless. Sad.
Amazing!
Wow!  This place is amazing, the space is super inviting, the drinks are great and the good is amazing. Welcome to dc.
Lobster taco is great. The cornbread is tasty as well. Decor and ambiance make this one of my favorite places as a newcomer to DC!

Mexicue is the latest New York City restaurant to call DC home. Stopped in here after reading all about it online and getting very hyped about the menu offerings! Everything looked amazing from the photos at the Chelsea location so I was excited because my beloved Meatball Shop, which previously operated out of this place, has closed.  Entering the restaurant, not much has changed from the last shop. Had a very awkward encounter with the hostess (?) who explained that since we didn’t have a reservation, we could sit “community style” with other people where you’re basically at the same table but not. Since there were only two of us, we thought it wasn’t a big deal.  We started with the seasonal guacamole which was guacamole, jalapeños and sesame seeds. This was basically two small scoops of guacamole for $12.50, which is an absurdly high price for such a small portion.  I ordered the kale and vegetable small plate and added shredded pork on it. I also got the romaine boat shrimp taco. The bowl was okay but pretty forgettable. The pork was VERY dry, like it had been sitting out for an hour or so.  The romaine boat taco was the highlight of the meal. The lettuce was crispy and the shrimp had a nice spicy flavor.  My boyfriend ordered a different bowl with barbecue pork and it was pretty decent but I think that’s because the barbecue salsa/sauce was overpowering the rest of the bowl.  Prices are a little too high for this food to not be amazing, in my opinion. Service was okay. Charging nearly $12 for a bowl that is as big as my very tiny hand is crazy though.  Not sure I’d come back unless it was for happy hour. Taco Bamba has way better quality at a better price point.
Poor greeting at door. Limited menu. one of my two items was cold as if it had been sitting. Bad service. Very noisy! Hope the next restaurant that goes into the space will be better.

Great atmosphere. That's pretty much it. The service was ok, servers were nice but drinks took a while, even though I was just ordering wine so they didn't have to do much. They didn't have my first choice of wine, a Cava, and that was also the only sparkling wine they offered by the glass. As appetizer I had the cornbread it was delicious. But then I ordered the chicken and the lobster tacos, not bad, but quite forgettable.

Run don’t walk to this place. Mexicue is my favorite spot in NYC and I screamed with glee when I learned they were coming to DC! I went there and tried everything I could. Their guacamole and queso are fantastic and their drinks are strong and tasty. You really can’t go wrong with anything here.

They haven't even been open 2 weeks yet and already they can't seem to get things in order. Sadly they might suffer the same fate as the meatball shop that was once there for the very short period of time.  This is my second time coming here and both times they didn't have something that's on their small menu. I specifically wanted some queso so I decided to try mexicue again for the second time hoping to get some of their classic nachos but once again they didn't have something this time they didn't have queso lmfaooo I mean how hard is queso. I left and went to Chipotle down the block and got me a bowl and queso  . Sadly this place isn't making a first good impression. How hard is it to have the items listed on your menu in stock

Food is tasty for sure. It is also all very rich. We got the breakfast tacos, grilled cornbread, pulled pork taco, and brisket tacos.  We would def do the breakfast tacos again. The pulled pork was tasty, but I thought the sauce on the brisket tacos were too much. I also loved the cornbread - sweet and accompanied with a savory hot butter. The brunch HH is a good deal at $6 for a Bloody Mary. Would totes return.  The restaurant itself is loud with poor sound insulation.
Very good food and nice atmosphere.

Chic Mexican x Southern BBQ spot in the Logan Circle area. I ordered three tacos and each one was phenomenal, especially the chicken and shrimp tacos. Service was also excellent. Lynn, the co-owner, was nice enough to show us around the place and tell us about her background. Looking forward to trying brunch!
Stylish and delicious. Beautiful presentation outside; sloppy Mexican w/ barbeque flare inside. Tapas portions. "The Cellar" deco is warm and smart.

Awesome place, and delicious modern Mexican food. The staff were very friendly and recommended their best dishes. The menu has some very nice vegetarian tacos and bowls. We tried the seasonal charred cauliflower and the grilled avocado taco and both were delicious. Food comes in slightly spicy, but only to the point to boosting all the other flavors. We'll definitely come back!
Great food, great atmosphere, friendly and attentive staff! The Nashville hot chicken taco was so good I didn’t want to ruin it by having my second taco.

Awesome dinner! The ambiance is fun and new, the service is friendly and helpful and the food is delicious (highly recommend the Mac and cheese). Our server, Ryan was great. Excited to have it in the neighborhood.
